				\begin{document}$$\begin{array}{c}MC=\frac{I(B)-I(0)}{I(0)}100 \% \\ MEL=\frac{EL(B)-EL(0)}{EL(0)}100 \% \end{array}$$\end{document}where I(B) and EL(B) are the device current and electroluminescence in the presence of a magnetic field B, respectively.
